House Health 1
Amendment No. 1 to HB2415
Terry
Signature of Sponsor
AMEND S e n ate Bill No. 2406* House Bill No. 2415
by deleting all language after the enacting clause and substituting:
SECTION 1. Tennessee Code Annotated, Title 68, Chapter 1, Part 1, is amended by
adding the following as a new section:
(a) As used in this section:
(1) "Hospital" has the same meaning as defined in § 68-11-201; and
(2) "Law enforcement officer" means an individual who is employed by a
local government as a member of the local government's law enforcement
agency and who is trained and actively engaged in police work for the
investigation into and detection of crime.
(b) The commissioner of health shall, subject to subsection (d), develop a
hospital security grant program to award grants to hospitals, as defined in § 68-11-201,
for the purpose of hiring off-duty law enforcement officers to serve as hospital security.
(c) The commissioner shall ensure that grants to hospitals pursuant to this
section are awarded in all three (3) grand divisions of this state, and such awards
include hospitals sited in both urban and rural locations.
(d) Funding for the grant program created by this section is subject to
appropriation by the general assembly.
SECTION 2. The commissioner of health is authorized to promulgate rules to effectuate
this act. The rules must be promulgated in accordance with the Uniform Administrative
Procedures Act, compiled in Tennessee Code Annotated, Title 4, Chapter 5.
SECTION 3. This act takes effect upon becoming a law, the public welfare requiring it.
